---
import { TAP_COUNT } from '../utils/constants';
---

<section class="section" id="story">
  <div class="split2">
    <div>
      <img class="photo story-img" src="/assets/photos/beer-flight-table.webp" alt="A flight of Gridiron beers on a wooden NB-shaped board" width="724" height="484" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
    </div>
    <div class="story-body">
      <span class="kicker reveal">Our Story</span>
      <h2 class="story-h reveal d1">Rooted<br />In Place</h2>
      <p class="reveal d1">Gridiron takes its name from the rushing rapids near our old family homestead—a wild stretch of the Kennebecasis River that's been part of our story for generations.</p>
      <p class="reveal d2">While family is the beating heart of this business, Gridiron has grown into something bigger. It's a gathering place. A welcoming space built on community, deep connections, and a shared love for great beer and even better company.</p>
      <p class="reveal d2">We brew our small-batch craft beer right here in Hampton, on the very shores of the Kennebecasis. Whenever we can, we pour local New Brunswick and Canadian grains into our vats, mixing them with the finest select ingredients from afar to get the perfect pint.</p>
      <p class="reveal d3">Proudly brewed in our hometown. Crafted with a deep respect for where we come from—and a raised glass to everyone who walks through our doors.</p>
      <div class="story-stats reveal d3">
        <div class="stat"><b>{TAP_COUNT}</b><span>Beers On Tap</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><b>100%</b><span>Brewed In Hampton</span></div>
        <div class="stat"><b>1</b><span>River Out Back</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
